      "content": "There is no consensus among mainstream economists, and the debate is far from settled, though the evidence is increasingly pointing toward the limitations of simple growth arguments. Many empirical studies suggest that tax cuts alone often fail to generate the broad-based growth necessary to significantly reduce inequality. The prevailing view among many progressive economists is that structural reforms, not just tax incentives, are needed to meaningfully address wealth disparities.",
      "source": "target",
