    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so if the growth arguments aren't really holding up based on the evidence, wouldn't that mean the supply-side approach is basically just an outdated theory at this point? like, if research shows it doesn't work, isn't it more accurate to say it's a failed policy rather than just a \"different perspective\"?",
