      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Calling the supply-side approach a \"failed policy\" is a strong judgment, but the empirical evidence certainly challenges its universal applicability. Mainstream economics has evolved to incorporate more sophisticated models that show the assumptions underpinning pure supply-side theory are often too simplistic. Instead of being entirely outdated, it is more accurately viewed as a theory that requires significant modification to account for modern realities like rising corporate concentration and wealth accumulation.",
      "source": "target",
